From: SRB2Kart PS Vita / PS TV port
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] http-mserv: guard logstream with LOGMESSAGES

`logstream` is only declared under `#ifdef LOGMESSAGES` (doomdef.h), which is
defined for Windows / Unix / macOS only. `http-mserv.c` uses it unconditionally,
so any *other* platform that builds with curl fails to compile:

    http-mserv.c: error: 'logstream' undeclared

Nobody had hit this because curl had never been built outside that list. Once
guarded, the master server and the server browser work fine on a console.

Found while porting SRB2Kart to the PS Vita / PS TV.
---
--- a/src/http-mserv.c
+++ b/src/http-mserv.c
@@ -203,9 +203,11 @@
 
 	if (cv_masterserver_debug.value)
 	{
 		curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_VERBOSE, 1L);
+#ifdef LOGMESSAGES
 		curl_easy_setopt(curl, CURLOPT_STDERR, logstream);
+#endif
 	}
 
 	if (M_CheckParm("-bindaddr") && M_IsNextParm())
 	{
